reviews.text: A nice environment but it closes early.

I usually always stop by a Starbucks to have my coffee, but this one in HK is NOT on the right standards. I like to come here to take a coffee work on my laptop, but this time I had a ridiculous 30 min wifi after spending more than HK$100. When I asked for another "activation code" I was declined and asked to buy more time. 

That's disappointing for someone spending more than $150 per month on this brand alone.
Coffee tastes as usual, but how wonderful it is that there’s one coffee shop right in your place of working

It's typical Starbucks. Modern, clean and comfortable but if you want coffee (or even a snack), walk the 1 minute across the road to One Little Room. 

I've never had a good coffee, it's relatively expensive, the food is not fresh. Apart from the decor and seating there is nothing worth coming here for.  For those currently rating this place 4/5-stars, do try One Little Room (less than 1 minute away) or even MG Café (5 mins down Hoi Bun Road) instead and see the difference.
Very nice place

The venue was large and spacious with nice decoration.  However, the location was far away from public transportation.
